WEBVTT

00:00:04.742 --> 00:00:05.677
Hey.

00:00:06.611 --> 00:00:08.179
Have you kissed anyone before?

00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:23.328
That day,

00:00:25.063 --> 00:00:26.898
the four of us committed a crime.

00:00:27.465 --> 00:00:28.900
The crime we committed

00:00:30.168 --> 00:00:33.438
was sealed away in a time capsule
that would never be opened in the future.

00:00:33.505 --> 00:00:37.308
Your son shoplifted from my store.

00:00:37.375 --> 00:00:39.777
The victim is Hideyuki Sakuma,
40 years old.

00:00:40.345 --> 00:00:41.312
Smile Sakuma…

00:00:41.379 --> 00:00:43.248
It's believed that Oshima's accomplice

00:00:43.314 --> 00:00:45.049
took the 30 million yen

00:00:45.116 --> 00:00:47.118
and Officer Kiyohara's gun,

00:00:47.185 --> 00:00:48.686
but the 30 million yen and the gun

00:00:49.187 --> 00:00:50.555
-were never found…
-The question is,

00:00:51.222 --> 00:00:53.057
who shot Oshima?

00:00:54.125 --> 00:00:55.527
I shot him.

00:00:57.595 --> 00:00:59.564
I don't think I deserve to be happy.

00:00:59.631 --> 00:01:01.099
I can't undo the fact…

00:01:02.267 --> 00:01:04.135
that I have committed a crime.

00:01:05.303 --> 00:01:06.871
Maki.

00:01:06.938 --> 00:01:09.807
That day,
I went to Sakuma's place by myself

00:01:10.408 --> 00:01:12.410
because that was the only option I had.

00:01:23.354 --> 00:01:24.689
Where's the gun?

00:01:25.323 --> 00:01:26.157
Sorry.

00:01:26.224 --> 00:01:29.761
Where's the gun? Where's the damn gun?!

00:01:37.001 --> 00:01:40.905
I shot the manager of Smile Sakuma
with a gun.

00:01:43.675 --> 00:01:44.709
I knew

00:01:45.510 --> 00:01:47.679
you'd bring the gun to me.

00:01:49.480 --> 00:01:50.648
Detective Tobina,

00:01:51.816 --> 00:01:55.353
there's a chance you didn't kill Oshima.

00:01:56.387 --> 00:01:59.057
We'll find that out
once we examine this gun.

00:02:04.963 --> 00:02:07.265
You retrieved the gun to help Junichi?

00:02:47.972 --> 00:02:48.873
Oh.

00:02:50.875 --> 00:02:52.944
I just thought of a great title.

00:02:54.746 --> 00:02:57.548
Deep breathing is important.

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:03.321
Oh man, that was close,
I wasn't breathing.

00:03:03.388 --> 00:03:05.823
Don't stop. Take a deep breath.

00:03:05.890 --> 00:03:07.425
Breathe. Deeply.

00:03:10.595 --> 00:03:12.297
It feels great.

00:03:12.363 --> 00:03:15.366
I forgot I have to take a deep breath
when I feel out of sorts.

00:03:15.433 --> 00:03:16.968
The body feels stiff, huh?

00:03:17.035 --> 00:03:19.437
That's right, that's right

00:03:20.238 --> 00:03:21.773
-It's a bath time song.
-Ms. Nara.

00:03:27.278 --> 00:03:28.212
Ms. Nara.

00:03:28.746 --> 00:03:30.114
Please close the door.

00:03:51.235 --> 00:03:52.303
What's going on?

00:03:55.039 --> 00:03:56.040
Right now,

00:03:58.209 --> 00:04:00.278
I'm going to check

00:04:02.046 --> 00:04:05.016
how many bullets are left in this gun.

00:04:05.583 --> 00:04:06.651
And that

00:04:07.618 --> 00:04:10.154
may reveal some new truths.

00:04:42.520 --> 00:04:44.555
There are three bullets remaining.

00:04:52.397 --> 00:04:53.431
Detective Tobina,

00:04:54.332 --> 00:04:57.969
we won't even discuss whether the bullet
you fired really hit Oshima or not,

00:04:58.603 --> 00:04:59.504
because you

00:05:00.505 --> 00:05:02.507
didn't even fire the gun.

00:05:04.475 --> 00:05:05.309
What?

00:05:05.877 --> 00:05:08.212
You were a sixth-grader at the time,

00:05:08.746 --> 00:05:12.884
and you had just discovered
the body of Officer Kiyohara,

00:05:12.950 --> 00:05:14.986
so you were in a state of shock.

00:05:17.155 --> 00:05:19.891
When a gunshot rang out nearby,

00:05:19.957 --> 00:05:23.294
you assumed it was you who had fired it.

00:05:24.762 --> 00:05:26.664
Is that not possible?

00:05:37.542 --> 00:05:39.677
Detective Inoue,
I'm going to borrow your car.

00:05:39.744 --> 00:05:40.578
Where are you going?

00:05:41.879 --> 00:05:43.047
Prefectural police headquarters.

00:05:47.051 --> 00:05:48.319
I'm Nagai.

00:05:48.386 --> 00:05:49.954
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

00:05:54.659 --> 00:05:56.427
Keisuke, you're okay with all this?

00:05:57.462 --> 00:05:59.096
Of course I'm not okay.

00:06:02.233 --> 00:06:05.069
When Masaki asked about Makiko
I didn't know what to say.

00:06:05.136 --> 00:06:07.271
I'll be here to protect you, Masaki.

00:06:09.073 --> 00:06:10.174
What about Mom?

00:06:12.577 --> 00:06:13.644
She'll be all right.

00:06:13.711 --> 00:06:15.146
We'll be with her.

00:06:15.646 --> 00:06:18.082
But Junichi answered in an instant.

00:06:19.417 --> 00:06:20.852
I was hit with the reality.

00:06:21.819 --> 00:06:24.155
I knew then I could never beat Junichi.

00:06:27.225 --> 00:06:28.493
It pissed me off too.

00:06:29.193 --> 00:06:33.297
As Masaki's father I wanted to be cool,
but I ended up looking pathetic.

00:06:33.364 --> 00:06:35.199
You can turn the tables in no time.

00:06:35.833 --> 00:06:39.837
You said you'd have Maki's mother help out
until Maki comes back,

00:06:40.671 --> 00:06:42.940
but wouldn't it be better for Masaki
to live with you?

00:06:44.375 --> 00:06:45.376
Oh…

00:06:46.177 --> 00:06:47.879
-Well…
-What? You can't?

00:06:52.383 --> 00:06:54.118
I hadn't told you yet, but…

00:06:56.921 --> 00:06:58.589
I remarried.

00:07:04.462 --> 00:07:05.296
When?

00:07:05.963 --> 00:07:07.164
A year ago.

00:07:09.267 --> 00:07:11.168
We're having a baby soon too.

00:07:14.972 --> 00:07:16.507
Maki didn't tell me about this.

00:07:16.574 --> 00:07:18.910
Makiko only found out recently.

00:07:21.712 --> 00:07:22.547
What?

00:07:29.520 --> 00:07:31.556
MITSUBA POLICE STATION

00:07:31.622 --> 00:07:32.790
Makiko Iwamoto

00:07:32.857 --> 00:07:35.426
has turned herself in
and admitted to killing Sakuma.

00:07:35.493 --> 00:07:38.396
The questioning will begin soon.

00:07:38.896 --> 00:07:40.231
And the gun?

00:07:41.032 --> 00:07:42.867
The police confiscated it.

00:07:43.367 --> 00:07:44.235
I see.

00:07:44.802 --> 00:07:47.905
I guess this wraps up this case.

00:07:47.972 --> 00:07:48.973
CHIEF KOSUGI

00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:50.241
You're testifying

00:07:51.742 --> 00:07:54.378
that when you refused his request for sex,

00:07:55.379 --> 00:07:56.981
he threatened you with a gun,

00:07:58.683 --> 00:08:00.084
and while you two fought,

00:08:01.085 --> 00:08:02.920
you picked up the gun

00:08:04.622 --> 00:08:07.425
and fired it when he came towards you.

00:08:09.126 --> 00:08:10.595
Is that correct?

00:08:13.731 --> 00:08:14.599
Yes.

00:08:17.301 --> 00:08:18.703
It's an unfortunate incident.

00:08:21.606 --> 00:08:23.541
You had no intention of killing him,

00:08:24.609 --> 00:08:26.644
but it just happened by accident.

00:08:28.412 --> 00:08:29.280
No.

00:08:30.448 --> 00:08:31.949
Do you finally remember

00:08:32.783 --> 00:08:33.884
who I am?

00:08:36.520 --> 00:08:39.090
This is fate.

00:08:41.859 --> 00:08:45.730
But I find that impertinent attitude
irresistible.

00:08:47.932 --> 00:08:49.200
At that moment,

00:08:52.737 --> 00:08:55.006
I had murderous intent.

00:09:01.212 --> 00:09:02.513
I would also

00:09:03.714 --> 00:09:05.516
want to kill someone

00:09:07.218 --> 00:09:10.655
who hurt me or someone I care about.

00:09:19.997 --> 00:09:20.998
Oh,

00:09:21.899 --> 00:09:23.768
after examining that gun,

00:09:24.602 --> 00:09:27.338
we found out that Detective Tobina
did not shoot anyone.

00:09:50.094 --> 00:09:51.629
This is what makes you cry?

00:09:57.468 --> 00:09:58.703
I see.

00:10:01.806 --> 00:10:02.940
You

00:10:03.774 --> 00:10:07.244
wanted to free Detective Tobina
from the guilt of murder.

00:10:08.612 --> 00:10:10.848
You wished to help him out
that badly, huh?

00:10:12.316 --> 00:10:13.384
But now

00:10:14.618 --> 00:10:17.621
you're going to be carrying
the guilt of murdering someone.

00:10:35.706 --> 00:10:36.707
She's ready.

00:10:42.313 --> 00:10:45.683
I'll be here all night, okay?

00:10:54.725 --> 00:10:56.360
KOTONO

00:10:59.530 --> 00:11:00.464
Sorry.

00:11:03.634 --> 00:11:04.468
What's wrong?

00:11:04.535 --> 00:11:06.137
My water broke.

00:11:06.203 --> 00:11:07.138
What?

00:11:07.738 --> 00:11:09.240
I called the hospital

00:11:09.774 --> 00:11:11.108
and they told me to come right away.

00:11:12.343 --> 00:11:13.778
Keisuke,

00:11:14.512 --> 00:11:15.813
where are you right now?

00:11:15.880 --> 00:11:18.449
Sorry, I'm in Mitsuba right now.

00:11:19.350 --> 00:11:20.384
I…

00:11:21.018 --> 00:11:22.753
I need to call a taxi, huh?

00:11:23.320 --> 00:11:25.489
-Can you call for a taxi?
-Okay, microwave.

00:11:25.556 --> 00:11:26.557
Yeah.

00:11:26.624 --> 00:11:28.893
-Two and a half minutes.
-I'll be there as soon as I can.

00:11:28.959 --> 00:11:29.860
Approximately.

00:11:30.561 --> 00:11:31.695
Bye.

00:11:32.429 --> 00:11:35.232
-Write, "It's chikuzenni."
-It's chikuzenni.

00:11:35.800 --> 00:11:37.201
My wife's water broke.

00:11:40.638 --> 00:11:42.006
Such bad timing.

00:11:42.573 --> 00:11:44.341
You should hurry up and go.

00:11:45.876 --> 00:11:47.178
I'll keep an eye on Masaki.

00:11:47.845 --> 00:11:48.813
Thanks.

00:12:00.024 --> 00:12:01.225
-Here.
-Okay.

00:12:05.062 --> 00:12:06.430
Hiromi.

00:12:06.497 --> 00:12:07.331
Thanks for everything.

00:12:10.401 --> 00:12:11.869
I'll stay here tonight.

00:12:13.637 --> 00:12:14.872
Okay.

00:12:15.439 --> 00:12:16.907
-Here.
-Thanks.

00:12:42.533 --> 00:12:44.368
Mom went to the police

00:12:46.670 --> 00:12:48.405
because she killed the supermarket guy?

00:12:51.775 --> 00:12:53.043
It is, right?

00:13:15.466 --> 00:13:16.734
Why did she kill him?

00:13:23.941 --> 00:13:26.043
She did something very bad, right?

00:13:35.486 --> 00:13:36.520
Mom

00:13:37.521 --> 00:13:39.490
told me not to bully people,

00:13:41.859 --> 00:13:43.327
so why did she kill him?

00:13:47.364 --> 00:13:48.632
How can she do something

00:13:50.034 --> 00:13:51.535
so awful?

00:13:54.672 --> 00:13:57.107
Hey! Tell me why!

00:14:09.119 --> 00:14:10.020
Masaki.

00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:17.227
Do you love your mom?

00:14:18.862 --> 00:14:20.197
I don't like

00:14:21.432 --> 00:14:22.800
murderers.

00:14:27.304 --> 00:14:28.605
I hate

00:14:29.606 --> 00:14:30.874
Mom.

00:14:31.608 --> 00:14:33.010
She's the worst.

00:14:52.963 --> 00:14:54.932
It's because I shoplifted.

00:14:56.200 --> 00:14:58.168
It's all my fault.

00:14:59.837 --> 00:15:03.507
It's all because I shoplifted.

00:15:13.884 --> 00:15:16.186
It's because I shoplifted.

00:15:18.122 --> 00:15:19.223
How's Masaki?

00:15:20.157 --> 00:15:21.225
He fell asleep.

00:15:21.892 --> 00:15:24.495
I'm glad. I was worried
since I heard him having a breakdown.

00:15:26.497 --> 00:15:28.732
Junichi, do you want coffee?

00:15:28.799 --> 00:15:29.800
Thanks.

00:15:35.272 --> 00:15:36.807
By the way,

00:15:36.874 --> 00:15:41.545
the police officer who helped us
in the forest 23 years ago

00:15:41.612 --> 00:15:43.013
is still working here, huh?

00:15:43.514 --> 00:15:45.115
Yeah. Chief Kosugi.

00:15:46.083 --> 00:15:47.017
You remember him?

00:15:47.084 --> 00:15:51.388
Yeah, because he was the first person
who helped me in the forest.

00:15:52.990 --> 00:15:53.891
What?

00:15:55.659 --> 00:15:56.627
What did you just say?

00:16:01.298 --> 00:16:02.533
Help!

00:16:06.637 --> 00:16:07.538
What's wrong?

00:16:08.439 --> 00:16:09.540
What's wrong?

00:16:09.606 --> 00:16:11.141
Um…

00:16:11.208 --> 00:16:12.042
What's the matter?

00:16:13.077 --> 00:16:15.946
-Um…
-What's wrong?

00:16:24.088 --> 00:16:24.922
Good morning.

00:16:24.988 --> 00:16:26.890
Things are pretty crazy.

00:16:26.957 --> 00:16:29.593
This is not a secret or anything,

00:16:29.660 --> 00:16:31.261
but Ms. Nara has been asking for you.

00:16:31.328 --> 00:16:34.064
Not just once, but two or three times!
What have you done?

00:16:34.665 --> 00:16:35.632
Because…

00:16:37.034 --> 00:16:37.868
Ms. Nara,

00:16:38.502 --> 00:16:39.536
I need to tell you something.

00:16:39.603 --> 00:16:42.506
INTERROGATION ROOM 1

00:17:02.960 --> 00:17:03.794
Come in.

00:17:03.861 --> 00:17:05.095
CHIEF'S OFFICE

00:17:05.162 --> 00:17:06.330
Excuse me.

00:17:06.396 --> 00:17:07.331
CHIEF KOSUGI

00:17:07.397 --> 00:17:08.398
Excuse me.

00:17:11.268 --> 00:17:14.304
The culprit turned out to be
Makiko Iwamoto?

00:17:15.038 --> 00:17:15.906
Yes.

00:17:18.542 --> 00:17:20.978
It must be tough for you, Tobina,
since she was your classmate.

00:17:21.879 --> 00:17:25.082
However,
I'm sure the late Officer Kiyohara

00:17:25.149 --> 00:17:28.819
is relieved that his missing gun
has been recovered.

00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:32.222
Please find out exactly how

00:17:32.756 --> 00:17:36.927
Makiko Iwamoto obtained the gun.

00:17:37.794 --> 00:17:41.832
There is something I would like
to confirm with you, Chief Kosugi,

00:17:41.899 --> 00:17:45.169
regarding how the gun was obtained.

00:17:45.669 --> 00:17:46.703
Me?

00:17:48.038 --> 00:17:50.674
Regarding the incident
that occurred 23 years ago,

00:17:50.741 --> 00:17:55.145
it was said at the time
that Oshima had an accomplice.

00:17:55.846 --> 00:17:58.081
Do you think there was an accomplice?

00:18:01.585 --> 00:18:04.755
The stolen 30 million yen was never found,

00:18:05.589 --> 00:18:08.225
and the investigation headquarters' view
at the time

00:18:08.992 --> 00:18:10.494
was that there was about

00:18:10.561 --> 00:18:13.363
an 80% chance that an accomplice
was involved.

00:18:13.430 --> 00:18:16.700
I believe without a doubt
there was an accomplice,

00:18:17.301 --> 00:18:20.103
and I think it was someone
within the police.

00:18:21.405 --> 00:18:22.639
Within the police?

00:18:23.407 --> 00:18:24.508
Yes.

00:18:27.544 --> 00:18:31.415
Please don't make
such accusations so lightly.

00:18:34.751 --> 00:18:39.223
Do you even have any proof?

00:18:40.424 --> 00:18:42.659
According to the investigation reports
from that time,

00:18:42.726 --> 00:18:46.263
multiple witnesses testified
that the robber

00:18:46.330 --> 00:18:49.266
fled towards the southern part
of the city.

00:18:49.800 --> 00:18:52.102
However, the robber was eventually found

00:18:52.169 --> 00:18:54.905
in Irohadai which is
in the northern part of the city.

00:18:57.007 --> 00:19:00.711
I believe this was due
to misleading reports from an accomplice.

00:19:02.946 --> 00:19:05.082
Posing as a regular citizen,

00:19:05.148 --> 00:19:07.818
the accomplice reported a sighting
of the robber

00:19:07.884 --> 00:19:10.387
and guided the police
to the southern part of the city.

00:19:11.822 --> 00:19:15.259
Meanwhile, in the unguarded
northern forest,

00:19:16.326 --> 00:19:19.730
the accomplice met up
with the perpetrator, Oshima.

00:19:21.265 --> 00:19:23.233
The purpose was probably

00:19:24.001 --> 00:19:25.402
to hand over the money.

00:19:31.208 --> 00:19:33.243
I think someone died.

00:19:34.645 --> 00:19:37.047
The bullet just happened
to hit that person.

00:19:37.114 --> 00:19:38.482
Yeah, that person died.

00:19:40.217 --> 00:19:41.184
Where's the money?

00:19:47.791 --> 00:19:49.326
We'll split the money later.

00:19:53.997 --> 00:19:55.766
Lay low for a while.

00:20:00.370 --> 00:20:01.371
Where's the gun?

00:20:03.140 --> 00:20:04.107
Where's the gun?

00:20:06.977 --> 00:20:08.812
Please give me more money.
This isn't enough.

00:20:12.816 --> 00:20:13.750
It's not bad.

00:20:13.817 --> 00:20:15.585
Yeah.

00:20:19.256 --> 00:20:21.858
If the accomplice was someone
in the police force,

00:20:21.925 --> 00:20:24.995
he could have informed Oshima
where the police were searching

00:20:25.062 --> 00:20:27.998
and skillfully guided him to the forest.

00:20:30.500 --> 00:20:31.968
They met in the forest,

00:20:34.137 --> 00:20:37.474
and the accomplice received money
from Oshima.

00:20:38.175 --> 00:20:41.244
Then, an unexpected incident occurred.

00:20:42.045 --> 00:20:43.747
The accomplice and Oshima were spotted

00:20:43.814 --> 00:20:46.183
by Officer Kazuo Kiyohara,
a local police officer

00:20:46.249 --> 00:20:49.286
who was also searching for the robber.

00:20:49.353 --> 00:20:50.987
-This isn't enough.
-Hey you two.

00:20:53.990 --> 00:20:55.025
It's the police.

00:20:55.625 --> 00:20:57.160
What are you guys doing there?

00:20:57.227 --> 00:21:00.664
Officer Kiyohara must have been surprised.

00:21:00.731 --> 00:21:03.233
After all,
he saw a man that looked like a robber,

00:21:03.834 --> 00:21:06.236
with none other than a police officer.

00:21:08.271 --> 00:21:09.773
Officer Kiyohara

00:21:10.374 --> 00:21:14.344
must have called out to the two of them,
trying to do his job.

00:21:15.312 --> 00:21:16.680
You, in the uniform,

00:21:17.981 --> 00:21:19.216
what are you doing?

00:21:22.652 --> 00:21:25.522
Following that, Officer Kiyohara

00:21:26.022 --> 00:21:29.292
was forced to fire two shots

00:21:29.793 --> 00:21:31.628
as a warning.

00:21:33.330 --> 00:21:34.765
Drop the gun!

00:21:42.339 --> 00:21:44.040
Freeze!

00:21:54.484 --> 00:21:56.820
Are you a police officer?

00:21:57.320 --> 00:21:58.321
Yes.

00:22:00.490 --> 00:22:01.725
Are you the section chief?

00:22:02.325 --> 00:22:03.160
And you are?

00:22:04.094 --> 00:22:05.896
I'm stationed at Irohadai.

00:22:05.962 --> 00:22:07.697
My name is Kazuo Kiyohara--

00:22:13.570 --> 00:22:14.805
The accomplice

00:22:15.539 --> 00:22:19.276
pointed the modified gun
at Officer Kiyohara

00:22:19.342 --> 00:22:21.044
and shot him dead.

00:22:30.987 --> 00:22:32.322
But then

00:22:33.223 --> 00:22:35.525
an unexpected person appears.

00:22:40.030 --> 00:22:43.600
Junichi Tobina, a sixth-grader.

00:22:45.836 --> 00:22:47.103
But then

00:22:47.604 --> 00:22:49.906
an unexpected person appears.

00:22:54.444 --> 00:22:58.081
Junichi Tobina, a sixth-grader.

00:22:58.782 --> 00:23:02.819
The accomplice
quickly hid in the shade of a nearby tree.

00:23:03.420 --> 00:23:05.355
The young boy arrived at the scene,

00:23:05.422 --> 00:23:08.458
and when he saw Officer Kiyohara's body,

00:23:08.525 --> 00:23:10.293
he realized what had happened.

00:23:13.463 --> 00:23:16.433
Then he saw Oshima.

00:23:25.375 --> 00:23:28.845
The boy then did something surprising.

00:23:28.912 --> 00:23:31.581
He picked up Officer Kiyohara's gun

00:23:32.782 --> 00:23:35.752
and pointed it at Oshima.

00:23:36.553 --> 00:23:40.590
The accomplice, who was watching
the scene unfold, must have been shocked.

00:23:45.495 --> 00:23:47.163
However, that accomplice

00:23:50.667 --> 00:23:53.036
aimed the gun at Oshima.

00:24:06.950 --> 00:24:07.951
Then you

00:24:11.054 --> 00:24:15.358
shot and killed Oshima
with your service pistol.

00:24:18.261 --> 00:24:19.996
You shot him,

00:24:20.530 --> 00:24:21.765
didn't you, Chief Kosugi?

00:24:26.636 --> 00:24:28.872
That's an interesting theory,

00:24:28.939 --> 00:24:31.207
but there's no objective facts.

00:24:40.050 --> 00:24:41.518
I have just that.

00:24:57.067 --> 00:24:59.703
The gun that Makiko Iwamoto was carrying

00:25:00.303 --> 00:25:05.108
was not Officer Kiyohara's gun
that went missing 23 years ago.

00:25:07.677 --> 00:25:08.612
Do you have proof?

00:25:10.246 --> 00:25:11.681
The number of remaining bullets.

00:25:14.284 --> 00:25:15.685
As you know,

00:25:15.752 --> 00:25:18.755
the New Nambu is a five-shot revolver.

00:25:19.456 --> 00:25:22.759
Two warning shots
were fired by Officer Kiyohara.

00:25:23.727 --> 00:25:26.830
Twenty-three years later,

00:25:26.896 --> 00:25:29.766
another bullet was fired to kill Sakuma.

00:25:30.533 --> 00:25:33.603
That leaves two remaining bullets.

00:25:33.670 --> 00:25:36.606
And if Detective Tobina had fired a shot,

00:25:36.673 --> 00:25:39.843
there would be one less bullet.

00:25:40.977 --> 00:25:42.045
However,

00:25:42.746 --> 00:25:45.782
the gun Makiko Iwamoto had
in her possession

00:25:46.983 --> 00:25:49.219
had three bullets left.

00:25:50.987 --> 00:25:54.391
In other words,
that gun is not Officer Kiyohara's.

00:25:59.095 --> 00:26:01.765
You switched the guns, right?

00:26:41.137 --> 00:26:42.372
Then

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:45.975
you took a big detour,

00:26:46.676 --> 00:26:50.346
met Naoto Sakuma in the forest,
and rescued him.

00:26:54.084 --> 00:26:55.285
Help!

00:26:59.022 --> 00:27:00.023
What's the matter?

00:27:01.758 --> 00:27:04.694
As the person in charge
of equipment management,

00:27:04.761 --> 00:27:07.597
you falsified the data
in the equipment ledger.

00:27:08.631 --> 00:27:10.266
In order to match the rifling marks,

00:27:10.333 --> 00:27:13.303
you switched the equipment numbers
of the gun

00:27:13.903 --> 00:27:17.340
that belonged to Officer Kiyohara,
with the gun you used to shoot Oshima.

00:27:20.443 --> 00:27:21.578
Believe it or not,

00:27:21.644 --> 00:27:24.481
when I checked the archives
at the prefectural police headquarters,

00:27:24.981 --> 00:27:26.216
I found

00:27:26.883 --> 00:27:30.653
that the original paper copy
was still available.

00:27:32.822 --> 00:27:36.392
This is the document before you changed
the equipment numbers.

00:27:58.515 --> 00:28:00.450
This is the prefectural police
headquarters.

00:28:00.517 --> 00:28:02.318
Chief Kosugi of Mitsuba Police Station,

00:28:02.385 --> 00:28:04.854
you're under arrest
for the murder 23 years ago.

00:28:04.921 --> 00:28:07.123
-What?
-This is the arrest warrant.

00:28:07.190 --> 00:28:08.158
Chief.

00:28:13.730 --> 00:28:15.098
Oh, boy.

00:28:16.166 --> 00:28:18.268
-Let's go.
-Wait.

00:28:18.768 --> 00:28:22.238
I want to correct and clarify one thing.

00:28:22.772 --> 00:28:25.842
I wasn't the accomplice.

00:28:26.643 --> 00:28:29.112
I don't want to be lumped together
with Oshima.

00:28:29.612 --> 00:28:31.848
I was the mastermind.

00:28:31.915 --> 00:28:33.416
Come.

00:28:40.890 --> 00:28:42.592
-Tobina.
-Stop it, Tobina!

00:28:44.127 --> 00:28:45.161
Hey!

00:28:45.995 --> 00:28:47.597
Why are you alive,

00:28:48.998 --> 00:28:50.433
while Pops is dead?

00:28:51.034 --> 00:28:52.735
-Why? Why?
-Calm down.

00:28:52.802 --> 00:28:54.437
Why?!

00:28:56.539 --> 00:28:58.408
Why?!

00:28:59.542 --> 00:29:00.710
Calm down!

00:29:02.946 --> 00:29:04.547
Calm down!

00:29:04.614 --> 00:29:05.982
MITSUBA KENDO CHAMPIONSHIP

00:29:08.952 --> 00:29:09.886
Have you ever had a dream

00:29:12.689 --> 00:29:14.591
about someone you killed… or who died?

00:29:18.027 --> 00:29:19.295
Nope.

00:29:20.597 --> 00:29:22.165
Thanks to you guys,

00:29:22.799 --> 00:29:24.467
I'll be on death row now.

00:29:25.568 --> 00:29:27.003
I'll appear in your dreams.

00:29:30.373 --> 00:29:32.475
I shouldn't have arrested you.

00:29:34.143 --> 00:29:36.312
I should've killed you with my own hands.

00:29:39.883 --> 00:29:42.185
Just calm down!

00:29:52.295 --> 00:29:55.565
Wow, it's so shocking.

00:29:55.632 --> 00:29:58.768
Who would've thought
that Chief Kosugi was the culprit?

00:30:00.003 --> 00:30:00.837
Yeah.

00:30:02.472 --> 00:30:04.908
Also, there's a rumor going around

00:30:05.408 --> 00:30:07.243
that Ms. Nara screamed?

00:30:08.811 --> 00:30:10.446
Yeah, she did.

00:30:10.513 --> 00:30:11.981
Why did she scream?

00:30:19.989 --> 00:30:21.257
I don't know either.

00:30:22.825 --> 00:30:24.294
Oh man.

00:30:24.360 --> 00:30:27.330
I bet she couldn't forgive the fact
that a police officer committed murder.

00:30:27.397 --> 00:30:29.165
That's not it, Detective Inoue.

00:30:31.868 --> 00:30:32.702
I'm Nagai.

00:30:36.906 --> 00:30:40.209
Do you know who the first victim was
in the incident

00:30:40.276 --> 00:30:42.011
23 years ago?

00:30:44.147 --> 00:30:46.716
The citizen who was hit by a stray bullet
at the bank, right?

00:30:53.456 --> 00:30:55.124
-Are you all right?
-Kurihara, are you all right?

00:30:55.191 --> 00:30:56.826
-Someone, call the ambulance!
-Kurihara.

00:30:56.893 --> 00:30:58.394
Akio Kurihara.

00:30:59.462 --> 00:31:01.264
He was my fiancé.

00:31:34.731 --> 00:31:36.733
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

00:31:39.168 --> 00:31:41.571
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

00:31:42.905 --> 00:31:43.906
Were you able to sleep?

00:31:49.545 --> 00:31:51.781
You won't have nightmares anymore, huh?

00:32:01.457 --> 00:32:02.325
I'm glad.

00:32:12.035 --> 00:32:14.637
Hiromi, you were the only one
who didn't ask me

00:32:17.273 --> 00:32:19.876
about my nightmares
or try to talk about the future.

00:32:21.744 --> 00:32:24.747
That helped me to feel at ease.

00:32:24.814 --> 00:32:25.648
Is that right?

00:32:25.715 --> 00:32:26.616
Yeah.

00:32:29.085 --> 00:32:31.788
I felt like it was okay for me to be here.

00:32:32.955 --> 00:32:34.791
I felt that I was accepted.

00:32:40.763 --> 00:32:42.665
Should we talk about the future?

00:32:47.770 --> 00:32:49.105
What do you want to do?

00:32:52.241 --> 00:32:55.978
This time, Makiko will have to bear
the guilt of having killed someone.

00:32:57.547 --> 00:32:58.581
I

00:32:59.549 --> 00:33:02.051
don't know what Makiko's verdict will be,

00:33:07.623 --> 00:33:09.025
but I want to support her.

00:33:16.132 --> 00:33:18.067
Just be honest and say that you like her.

00:33:23.739 --> 00:33:24.707
Okay.

00:33:28.711 --> 00:33:30.646
I'll be leaving this town.

00:33:41.324 --> 00:33:42.325
Bye.

00:33:43.226 --> 00:33:45.328
Bye. Thank you.

00:34:02.578 --> 00:34:03.579
Junichi.

00:34:11.754 --> 00:34:12.855
I love you.

00:34:14.757 --> 00:34:17.593
Spin me around.

00:34:18.227 --> 00:34:19.729
Since this is the last time.

00:34:21.697 --> 00:34:22.865
Makiko Iwamoto

00:34:23.432 --> 00:34:25.401
has been indicted
and next it will be the trial.

00:34:26.736 --> 00:34:27.703
Yes.

00:34:27.770 --> 00:34:30.039
Our buddy partnership
will be dissolved, huh?

00:34:31.274 --> 00:34:33.142
I'm so grateful to you, Ms. Nara.

00:34:33.943 --> 00:34:35.411
Thank you very much.

00:34:37.380 --> 00:34:40.082
Just like you,
whenever I tried to move forward,

00:34:40.149 --> 00:34:44.420
I found myself
being pulled back to 23 years ago.

00:34:45.188 --> 00:34:47.123
That's how it was for me
the last 23 years.

00:34:50.493 --> 00:34:54.063
In your case, you found out
that you never killed anyone.

00:34:54.697 --> 00:34:56.265
But in my case,

00:34:56.332 --> 00:34:59.268
the fact that my fiancé died
remains unchanged.

00:35:01.237 --> 00:35:02.238
However,

00:35:03.105 --> 00:35:07.577
I realized that maybe
I'm also making wrong assumptions,

00:35:07.643 --> 00:35:09.145
so I thought about it a bit.

00:35:10.146 --> 00:35:11.080
I see.

00:35:12.982 --> 00:35:14.183
I

00:35:15.184 --> 00:35:17.720
will never find a man
who's as good as Kurihara.

00:35:20.289 --> 00:35:21.224
What do you say to that?

00:35:25.361 --> 00:35:26.529
That's an assumption.

00:35:27.630 --> 00:35:28.564
Really?

00:35:29.065 --> 00:35:29.899
Yes.

00:35:31.367 --> 00:35:32.902
That's definitely an assumption.

00:35:36.806 --> 00:35:38.007
Excuse me.

00:35:38.074 --> 00:35:39.642
May I sit here?

00:35:39.709 --> 00:35:40.543
Sure, of course.

00:35:40.610 --> 00:35:41.777
Thank you.

00:35:47.316 --> 00:35:48.150
Yes?

00:35:50.286 --> 00:35:51.420
It's salted salmon.

00:35:52.255 --> 00:35:53.889
Oh, salted salmon?

00:35:54.590 --> 00:35:55.791
I like that.

00:35:58.094 --> 00:35:59.895
Do you come here often?

00:36:01.030 --> 00:36:03.065
Once in a while.

00:36:17.146 --> 00:36:18.681
We won't be able to see each other
for a while.

00:36:25.087 --> 00:36:26.389
Masaki

00:36:28.658 --> 00:36:30.760
is still unable to leave the house,

00:36:32.928 --> 00:36:34.096
but he's fine.

00:36:34.730 --> 00:36:36.432
He's eating all his meals every day.

00:36:48.044 --> 00:36:48.911
You know…

00:36:51.480 --> 00:36:53.849
a long time ago, when I was moving away,

00:36:54.817 --> 00:36:56.919
you said you'd see me off,
but I was rude to you.

00:36:57.853 --> 00:36:59.221
I'm sorry.

00:37:04.627 --> 00:37:07.229
When I was 20, I was in Yokohama too,

00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:12.601
and I actually knew

00:37:13.102 --> 00:37:16.472
that you were working part-time
at that cafe.

00:37:29.485 --> 00:37:31.187
I was never able to tell you
that I like you.

00:37:39.128 --> 00:37:40.196
Makiko,

00:37:45.167 --> 00:37:46.068
I love you.

00:38:14.363 --> 00:38:15.331
Keisuke.

00:38:15.831 --> 00:38:16.665
Yeah?

00:38:20.069 --> 00:38:21.637
When Makiko comes back,

00:38:23.606 --> 00:38:24.607
I'm planning on asking her

00:38:26.942 --> 00:38:28.444
to live with me.

00:38:31.046 --> 00:38:32.314
With Masaki too.

00:38:35.351 --> 00:38:36.786
Why are you reporting this to me?

00:38:38.454 --> 00:38:40.556
It's for Makiko and Masaki to decide.

00:38:41.390 --> 00:38:44.693
I have no say in who they live with.

00:38:45.561 --> 00:38:46.395
What about you, Naoto?

00:38:47.029 --> 00:38:48.063
You have anything to say?

00:38:51.333 --> 00:38:52.301
No.

00:38:54.670 --> 00:38:56.305
I think Maki will be happy.

00:39:03.379 --> 00:39:05.114
It still pisses me off though.

00:39:08.918 --> 00:39:11.220
My dad became Pops to you,

00:39:11.287 --> 00:39:13.722
and now you want to live with my son?

00:39:15.424 --> 00:39:18.694
My dad loved you,
and my son is attached to you too.

00:39:18.761 --> 00:39:20.196
Of course I don't like that.

00:39:22.765 --> 00:39:23.599
And now

00:39:24.467 --> 00:39:26.635
you're going to live with Makiko?

00:39:29.138 --> 00:39:32.141
I wouldn't be able to handle Makiko
as she carries the burden of her crime.

00:39:32.775 --> 00:39:33.943
What's more,

00:39:34.009 --> 00:39:35.678
if I knew back then that Makiko

00:39:35.744 --> 00:39:38.013
had been raped,
I wouldn't have been able to handle it.

00:39:39.415 --> 00:39:42.451
But I'm sure you would've been able to,
Junichi.

00:39:42.518 --> 00:39:44.320
You keep popping up in my head like that.

00:39:45.387 --> 00:39:47.590
I'm sick and tired
of comparing myself to you!

00:39:49.658 --> 00:39:51.126
What am I, chopped liver?

00:39:52.728 --> 00:39:54.330
How is that my fault?

00:40:00.569 --> 00:40:02.338
It pisses me off.

00:40:07.243 --> 00:40:08.344
Junichi.

00:40:10.846 --> 00:40:12.515
Please help support Masaki.

00:40:23.692 --> 00:40:24.860
All right.

00:40:30.132 --> 00:40:31.867
ONE YEAR LATER

00:40:31.934 --> 00:40:33.202
-Venezuela.
-Caracas.

00:40:33.936 --> 00:40:34.770
Mongolia.

00:40:35.404 --> 00:40:36.405
Ulaanbaatar.

00:40:36.472 --> 00:40:37.740
Nice.

00:40:39.475 --> 00:40:40.509
India.

00:40:41.310 --> 00:40:44.280
-What?
-You're making no sense.

00:40:44.346 --> 00:40:45.347
Why?

00:40:53.155 --> 00:40:54.557
Yes, please proceed with that.

00:40:55.824 --> 00:40:59.762
So far, no major issues
have been raised by the inspection agency.

00:41:00.663 --> 00:41:03.766
We are also finalizing the preliminary
exterior design plans as well.

00:41:03.832 --> 00:41:04.433
JUNICHI TOBINA

00:41:04.500 --> 00:41:05.501
By concentrating

00:41:06.135 --> 00:41:08.370
construction vehicles on the south side,

00:41:09.038 --> 00:41:10.172
we can reduce the…

00:41:10.239 --> 00:41:11.473
Makiko's sentence has been decided.

00:41:12.508 --> 00:41:14.376
Three years imprisonment for murder.

00:41:15.377 --> 00:41:16.512
Five years suspension.

00:41:41.604 --> 00:41:45.007
KANAGAWA DETENTION CENTER

00:41:59.855 --> 00:42:00.990
You came?

00:42:10.232 --> 00:42:11.100
Let's go.

00:42:18.307 --> 00:42:20.809
The crimes we sealed in the past
were brought to light.

00:42:22.678 --> 00:42:24.013
Our lives were

00:42:25.481 --> 00:42:27.016
shaken up.

00:42:33.489 --> 00:42:34.690
Junichi.

00:42:35.924 --> 00:42:36.759
Yeah?

00:42:39.928 --> 00:42:41.196
Thank you.

00:42:52.007 --> 00:42:53.108
Hey.

00:42:55.444 --> 00:42:56.278
Yeah?

00:42:57.913 --> 00:42:59.481
Have you kissed anyone before?

00:43:06.388 --> 00:43:07.423
What?

00:43:09.992 --> 00:43:12.161
What is it all of a sudden?

00:43:12.728 --> 00:43:13.729
Right then,

00:43:15.130 --> 00:43:16.799
the door to the future…

00:43:20.836 --> 00:43:22.037
softly opened.

00:44:09.051 --> 00:44:10.853
THIS DRAMA IS A FICTION

00:44:10.919 --> 00:44:12.788
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita